<subSubSection id="5343C12AA2316A39A150FCE1506CBA60" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="C954B54C8116A7F0E9760F1F482C7C3B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="80C6B642E630CB17EA56D3E0F68C0372" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="5CEDECAF12D6921DE5BEDBEA22FE5CE1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum procumbens" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procumbens">
<emphasis id="91051F1F34BE1E2E710D08E975216EE0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum procumbens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a plant of open places in many forest types, often scrambling over other vegetation and on rocks, from sea level to 650(1,500) m elevation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
